tool_description: Given an image, returns the positions of facial features (eyes, nose, lips etc) for each face in the image.
name: Face Landmarks
title: Face Landmarks

api_list.name: DetectLandmarksFromURL
api_list.description:
Detects Face Landmarks from URL of an image. Url has to be passed in the POST body as JSON.
{ "url" :  <url to image> }.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://face-landmarks.p.rapidapi.com/DetectLandmarksFromURL"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "face-landmarks.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
